Exact blocker
  src/bin/realtime_acceptance.rs constructs CpalAudioBackend with
  CpalAudioOptions::default(). src/audio_native_cpal.rs defines that default as
  preferred_sample_rate=48000 and preferred_buffer_frames=256. There is no CLI
  argument or environment-variable override for the requested buffer size.
  negotiate_format() calls choose_buffer_frames(256, input_range, output_range).
  Both actual default devices expose a 15..4096 frame range, so the clamp result
  is exactly 256 frames, not 128. A 7200-second invocation of this binary would
  therefore run at 48 kHz / 256 frames and cannot produce the requested 128-frame
  acceptance evidence.

Run and evidence disposition
  The 7200-second audio run was not started because native hardware negotiation
  deterministically cannot select 128 with this unmodified binary. No shortened
  run was used. acceptance-evidence/performance/128.json was not written. Schema
  and performance-threshold validation are not applicable without a qualifying
  48 kHz / 128-frame run. No passing evidence was fabricated.
